				\begin{document}$${J}_{m}$$\end{document} from 13.08 to 15.41 mA cm−2. These increments in current densities indicated that photons absorbed were reflected into the active region, and, re-harvesting occurred thanks to the photonic band gap designed in NIR. Consequently, FF\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
